file=Brand Studio/spark/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: spark-logical-book-requirements\ntype: logical\nstatus: built — inherits from Shared OS (2026-07-15)\nassigned_agent: spark (Brand Studio / Creative Director — department leader)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\ndate_filled: 2026-07-15\n · p:=Logical artifacts are Python scripts in `Shared OS/logical/` (playbook §13.5). Spark inherits the department-shared `marketing_laws.py`. All dedicated scripts are paywall-blocked pending Route D .md files. This file is the only file in this folder.\n · tb=\| # \| Script \| Source Book 1 \| Book 1 URL \| Source Book 2 \| Book 2 URL \| Route \| · tb=\|---\|--------\|--------------\|------------\|---------------\|------------\|-------\| · tb=\| 1 \| `marketing_laws.py` \| Ries & Trout, *The 22 Immutable Laws of Marketing* (1993) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/22immutablelawso00alri) — FREE \| Cialdini, *Pre-Suasion* (2016) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/presuasionrevolu0000cial) — FREE \| B \| · s(o:Scripts (Shared OS/logical/)=Additional free sources in `marketing_laws.py`: Pareto (1896), Marshall (1890), Bernays (1928), Campbell (1949), Zipf (1949) — public domain; Lasswell (1948), Hick (1952), Zajonc (1968), Von Restorff (1933) — academic papers. 10 free books/papers total.\n · tb=\| Script \| Source Book \| Book URL \| Why Spark Needs It \| · tb=\|--------\|------------\|----------\|---------------------\| · tb=\| `marketing_laws.py` \| Ries & Trout + Cialdini + 8 free sources \| See above \| Grounds the critique's 1-10 axes and gate checklist with empirical marketing laws \| · tb=\| Previously Flagged (0.6) \| Status \| Script \| · tb=\|--------------------------\|--------\|--------\| · tb=\| critique's five 1-10 axes — craft rubrics, not validated instruments \| ✅ Cleared \| `marketing_laws.py` — `law_of_perception` (perception vs reality), `law_of_focus` (word ownership), `von_restorff_effect` (distinctiveness) \| · tb=\| gate checklist — craft rubric without empirical grounding \| ✅ Cleared \| `marketing_laws.py` — `lasswell_model` (communication completeness check for every creative) \| · tb=\| "6/10 concept" — disciplined opinion not verified \| ✅ Cleared \| `marketing_laws.py` — `law_of_the_category` (category creation vs variation), `law_of_leadership` (first-ness advantage) \| · sts:Skills to Script Mapping=- **creative-critique** — imports `marketing_laws.py` (`law_of_perception`, `law_of_focus`, `von_restorff_effect`) for concept/coherence axis grounding\n- **creative-gate** — imports `marketing_laws.py` (`lasswell_model`, `law_of_the_category`) for communication structure and category positioning checks\n · tb=\| Script \| Blocked By \| Source Needed \| · tb=\|--------\|-----------\|---------------\| · tb=\| Dedicated advertising effectiveness script \| Paywalled book \| Empirical advertising effectiveness source with data linking creative qualities to outcomes (e.g., Binet & Field, *The Long and the Short of It*) \| · tb=\| Dedicated Ogilvy extraction script \| Paywalled book \| Ogilvy, *Ogilvy on Advertising* or *Confessions of an Advertising Man* \| · sp:Still Pending=These require Route D .md files from paywalled sources before extraction can proceed.\n